Continuously Compounded Returns
\[
\begin{gathered}
P_{t}=P_{0} e^{r_{0, T}} \\
r_{0, T}=\ln \left(\frac{P_{t}}{P_{0}}\right) \\
r_{0, T}=r_{0,1}+r_{1,2}+\cdots+r_{T-2, T-1}+r_{T-1, T}
\end{gathered}
\]

Variance of a Random Variable
\[
\begin{aligned}
\sigma^{2}(X) & =E[X-E(X)]^{2} \\
& =\sum_{i=1}^{n} P\left(X_{i}\right)[X-E(X)]^{2}
\end{aligned}
\]

Conditional Variance of a Random Variable
\[
\begin{gathered}
\sigma^{2}(X \mid S)=P\left(X_{1} \mid S\right)\left[X_{1}-E\left(X_{1} \mid S\right)\right]^{2}+P\left(X_{2} \mid S\right)\left[X_{2}-E\left(X_{2} \mid S\right)\right]^{2}+\cdots \\
+P\left(X_{n} \mid S\right)\left[X_{n}-E\left(X_{n} \mid S\right)\right]^{2}
\end{gathered}
\]

